The presence of hydrothecae on the hydrocaulus is the main defining character of the family 

Halopterididae 
Millard, 1962

(
Millard 1962
, 1975; 
Schuchert 1997
), and the generic limits within the family are largely based on the shape of the colonies and their ramification patterns (
Schuchert 1997
).
